docTitle.titlePart: Íslensk lögbók hvörja saman hefur skrifað og útgefið Magnús kóngur son Hákonar kóngs
Hvör að til heyrir ærlegum vísum og velöktuðum höfðingsmanni Matthías Guðmu[n]dssyni
Skrifuð af Guðmundi Jónssyni á Fróðá um veturinn anno 1665

foliation.p: Foliated by scribe 1-147, but pages between 103 and 104, 110 and 111 skipped, and 121 written twice. Four last pages are unfoliated.

decoNote.p: Title page decorated with red and blue.
Chapter headings written in red ink, and chapter numbers and occasional large letters written or decorated with red.
Initials written with red, green or blue. Large initials on ff. 2v, 6r, 9r, 10r, 20r, 22r, 28r, 32v, 35v, 53v, 57v, 64r and 71r.

binding.p: Brown leather binding with cardboards; young spine.

provenance.p: The manuscript was written for sheriff Matthías Guðmundsson and belonged to him.
The John Rylands Library bought the Bibliotheca Lindesiana, the manuscript collection of the earls of Crawford, in 1901, including the manuscripts bearing the shelfmarks Icelandic MS 1-4.
The manuscript is preserved at the John Rylands Research Institute and Library in Manchester.

source.p: Halldóra Kristinsdóttir catalogued on February 2nd 2026. Built on the cataloguing of Ólafs Halldórssonar, see Skrá yfir íslenzk handrit í Cambridge, London, Manchester, Leeds og Dublin.

additional.surrogates: The manuscript was digitized in Manchester in 2025 and copies of the images given to the National and University Library of Iceland to be published on its manuscript website.
